      "content": "I got a bit carried away with the goblin's treasure chest. To clarify, the p-value represents the probability of observing a result as extreme or more extreme than the one you obtained, assuming that the null hypothesis is true. In other words, it's the probability of getting a result as unusual or unlikely as yours, if the null hypothesis is actually true. Think of it like this: if you were to repeat the experiment many times, what percentage of those repetitions would you expect to get a result as extreme or more extreme than yours, if the null hypothesis is true?",
